Virtual Career Center Implementation: This position will project manage the implementation (creation and integration) of a large-scale virtual career center system.

The multi-phase project will include:
A baseline platform where users can develop a resume, search for job openings, view supplemental information, explore new careers, connect to training opportunities, list job opportunities, and track candidates (businesses). This tool will leverage artificial intelligence/machine learning and integrate with existing case management systems.
A system/tool to organize virtual meetings and events for one-on-one staff appointments and large-scale presentations and training events
A scheduling tool, to assign appointments to the appropriate appointment type and office location.
The Project Manager will work closely with the Program Manager and agency leads.
Daily activities will include but not be limited to:
Facilitating successful completion of IT projects by working across project team boundaries in a matrix environment to secure resources, resolve issues, and set project timelines and milestones.
Manage project using a Project Management Body of Knowledge (PMBOK) based project management methodology containing well-defined and documented processes, templates, and guidelines for all project phases, the adherence to which is required and managed by a formal Project Management Office.
Prepare and manage Project Management Plan including but not limited to scope statement, schedule, budget, quality plan, risks, issues and communication plan, etc.
Prepare and deliver executive-level documents including presentations, proposals, and training materials; · Track Project performance to ensure goals are being met;
Identify and facilitate communications with stakeholder groups;
Utilize formal project change process and communicate all changes with all stakeholders;
Communication of project status and updates at all levels of the organization, with internal stakeholders, project team, and executive staff;
Develop and manage project budget, ensuring no cost overruns;
Coordinate with agency executives, project team members, portfolio staff, and other stakeholders;
Identify and mitigate project risks; escalate and resolve issues impacting project success;
Provide weekly, bi-weekly, and/or monthly status updates to executives within the agency and ITS;
Provide regular updates using the prescribed project management tool;
Coordinate with ITS Enterprise Chief Portfolio Office as needed;
Develop transition plan(s) and execute those plans to ensure an orderly transition to the agency including proper mentoring and training as needed to ensure a successful transition;
Provide identification and maintenance of critical path and contingencies;
Provide resource allocation estimating and reporting

Requirements:
Project Management Professional (PMP) certification or equivalent PM credential/education.
48 months experience managing a portfolio of interdependent Information Technology (IT) projects for the public sector/government.
84 months experience managing cross-functional, multi-year IT projects including oral and written communications with all stakeholders; with a focus on application development, vendor software implementation, and/or technology infrastructure projects.
84 months of experience tracking project deliverables, maintaining project budgets, managing procurements, maintaining vendor relationships, managing stakeholder relationships, tracking and resolving project risks and issues using the Project Management Body of Knowledge (PMBOK) project management methodology.
84 months experience managing and implementing projects utilizing industry-standard development life cycle methodologies; with a focus on iterative project planning and application development/execution.


About Ann Enterprises, Inc. (dba AnnSolutions.com):

